  "commentary": "With SPX at 6604.58 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6610, dealers are currently in PIN regime and likely selling into any strength toward the massive +93.2B gamma wall at 6610. The thick positive gamma cushion from 6605-6620 creates a strong mean-reversion environment where rallies get sold and dips get bought, with 6590 as the key negative gamma support level where dealer buying would accelerate any bounce.\n\nThe gex_surge event combined with spot trading in the heart of positive gamma territory suggests we're in a high-conviction stabilization zone, with 6610 acting as immediate resistance and 6590 as the critical floor to hold.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to chop sideways between 6590-6610 with limited breakout potential.",
